<div class="related related-articles">
<h2>Find out more</h2>

 <ul>
<li><a href="http://www.bis.gov.uk/" target="_blank" title="Link to the Department for Innovation, Universities and Skills website">Department for Innovation, Universities and Skills</a> outlines the government's further and higher education policy and science policy and offers support for science and technology</li>
<li><a href="http://www.hefce.ac.uk/" target="_blank" title="Link to HEFCE website">HEFCE </a>(Higher Education Funding Council for England) distributes public money for teaching and research to universities and colleges</li>
<li><a href="http://www.hepi.ac.uk/" target="_blank" title="Link to the Higher Education Policy Institute website">HEPI</a> (Higher Education Policy Institute)&nbsp;aims to ensure that UK higher education policy development&nbsp;is informed by research and by knowledge</li>
<li><a href="http://www.hesa.ac.uk/" target="_blank" title="Link to HESA website">HESA</a>&nbsp; (Higher Education Statistics Agency) is the central source of UK higher education statistics</li>
<li><a href="http://www.rcuk.ac.uk/" target="_blank" title="Link to Research Councils UK website">Research Councils UK</a> provides links to all the UK research councils</li>
<li><a href="http://www.ucas.ac.uk/" target="_blank" title="Link to UCAS website">UCAS</a> (University and Colleges Admission Service) offers advice and information about the University application process</li>
<li><a href="http://unistats.direct.gov.uk/" target="_blank" title="Link to the Unistats website">Unistats</a> to help make an informed choice when deciding which university or college to apply to</li>
<li><a href="http://www.universitiesuk.ac.uk/Pages/Default.aspx" target="_blank" title="Link to Universities UK website">Universities UK</a> aims to promote and support the work of UK universities</li>
</ul>
</div>

